==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Troupial
<hw>Troup"i*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>troupiale</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous
species of bright-colored American birds belonging to <gen>Icterus</gen>
and allied genera, especially <spn>Icterus icterus</spn>, a native of
the West Indies and South America. Many of the species are called
<stype>orioles</stype> in America.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>troopial</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trouse</ent>⟦br⟧
